You can create expressions to set calculated values and evaluate data across multiple fields using a Formula or Aggregate element. For example, you may want to determine if the date entered for a qualifying life event is within thirty days of today's date.

Formula and Aggregate elements support constants and types:
OmniScript elements and JSON nodes
Numbers and integers
String literals
Booleans
Arrays
Dates

To prevent a date from being interpreted, set the Data Type to Text.
